1
00:00:10,133 --> 00:00:12,133
<i>This was the house
I used to dream of.</i>

2
00:00:12,267 --> 00:00:14,200
<i>We already have
a demolition order, Ma'am.</i>

3
00:00:14,333 --> 00:00:17,467
<i> We're asking you to cooperate,</i>

4
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:19,833
<i>so this doesn't turn
into a mess!</i>

5
00:00:21,333 --> 00:00:24,333
<i>I thought this was where
we'd build a happy family</i>

6
00:00:24,467 --> 00:00:26,200
<i> and make beautiful memories.</i>

7
00:00:26,333 --> 00:00:28,000
<i> But as it burns down,</i>

8
00:00:28,133 --> 00:00:31,500
<i>it feels like
all the dark secrets</i>

9
00:00:31,633 --> 00:00:33,300
<i>it's been hiding are coming out,
too.</i>

10
00:00:33,433 --> 00:00:35,067
<i> Why did you change your mind?</i>

11
00:00:35,233 --> 00:00:38,167
<i>One of our colleagues
referred us to Miss Castillo.</i>

12
00:00:38,300 --> 00:00:40,367
<i> You mean Marj Castillo?</i>

13
00:00:40,500 --> 00:00:42,567
<i> I'm not letting this go.</i>

14
00:00:42,700 --> 00:00:43,600
<i> Yes?</i>

15
00:00:43,733 --> 00:00:45,300
<i>You're the one
I want to talk to.</i>

16
00:00:45,433 --> 00:00:46,400
<i> About what?</i>

17
00:00:47,500 --> 00:00:48,733
<i> Are you Marj Castillo?</i>

18
00:00:48,867 --> 00:00:50,667
<i> How did you know my name?</i>

19
00:00:50,800 --> 00:00:53,433
<i>I've been hearing
a lot about you.</i>

20
00:01:00,033 --> 00:01:02,900
You know, this house is actually
perfect for your family.

21
00:01:03,033 --> 00:01:06,267
All the appliances
and furniture you see

22
00:01:06,400 --> 00:01:08,033
are included in the package.

23
00:01:08,200 --> 00:01:09,433
Later, when the others arrive,

24
00:01:09,567 --> 00:01:13,033
I'll show you the bedrooms,
including the kids' rooms.

25
00:01:13,167 --> 00:01:16,900
It's too bad your husband
couldn't make it.

26
00:01:18,033 --> 00:01:20,133
He said he's busy at work.

27
00:01:20,267 --> 00:01:21,667
That's probably...

28
00:01:21,800 --> 00:01:23,000
just his excuse.

29
00:01:23,133 --> 00:01:28,100
Because I've heard he's been
doing a lot of shady things here

30
00:01:33,067 --> 00:01:34,700
I guess
we can start the tour now?

31
00:01:34,833 --> 00:01:36,133
Wait. Wait!

32
00:01:43,200 --> 00:01:44,700
Sorry for the trouble, Randall.

33
00:01:44,833 --> 00:01:47,333
Jobert's been cranky
all morning.

34
00:01:47,467 --> 00:01:49,200
He wants to see his sister.

35
00:01:49,333 --> 00:01:51,167
It's okay, Auntie.

36
00:01:51,833 --> 00:01:54,267
Thank you, Randall.

37
00:01:55,500 --> 00:01:58,400
If I hadn't come all
the way to Batangas,

38
00:01:58,533 --> 00:01:59,467
I wouldn't have discovered

39
00:01:59,600 --> 00:02:01,567
that my husband
was already having an affair

40
00:02:01,700 --> 00:02:04,133
with another woman.

41
00:02:07,167 --> 00:02:08,333
After we say hi to your sister,

42
00:02:08,467 --> 00:02:09,567
we'll go back to sightseeing,
okay?

43
00:02:09,700 --> 00:02:11,067
- Yeah.
- Okay?

44
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:13,800
- Yes, bro.
- Behave inside, Jobert, okay?

45
00:02:13,967 --> 00:02:15,767
I will.

46
00:02:15,900 --> 00:02:17,933
Very good.

47
00:02:18,067 --> 00:02:21,000
Excuse me, Ma'am.
I'm just here to work.

48
00:02:21,133 --> 00:02:23,633
Please take your personal
problems somewhere else.

49
00:02:23,767 --> 00:02:25,367
I have no connection to that.

50
00:02:25,500 --> 00:02:27,233
Are you sure?

51
00:02:29,867 --> 00:02:31,967
Jobert.

52
00:02:32,100 --> 00:02:34,333
- Oh, there's your sister.
- Marj.

53
00:02:34,467 --> 00:02:35,500
Thanks, Randall.

54
00:02:35,633 --> 00:02:37,967
Wow, this place is huge.

55
00:02:38,100 --> 00:02:40,533
- Marj, babe, Jobert's here.
- Sis!

56
00:02:40,667 --> 00:02:43,767
Babe? Wow!

57
00:02:44,867 --> 00:02:47,867
That's a sweet pet name
you've got there, Randall.

58
00:02:49,667 --> 00:02:52,300
Randall, do you know her?

59
00:02:52,433 --> 00:02:54,433
Oh, yeah.

60
00:02:54,567 --> 00:02:56,567
Very well.

61
00:02:56,700 --> 00:03:01,067
Because I am this man's wife.

62
00:03:01,200 --> 00:03:05,300
And I am the mother
of his children.

63
00:03:05,433 --> 00:03:08,167
So you should be ashamed
of yourself

64
00:03:08,300 --> 00:03:12,033
for destroying our family!

65
00:03:12,167 --> 00:03:13,833
Is what she's saying true?

66
00:03:15,267 --> 00:03:17,000
Is she your wife?

67
00:03:18,300 --> 00:03:19,933
Poor Marj.

68
00:03:20,067 --> 00:03:21,200
Let's see

69
00:03:21,367 --> 00:03:26,400
if she can still brag once
her perfect life falls apart.

70
00:04:17,667 --> 00:04:20,100
Look at this homewrecker!

71
00:04:20,233 --> 00:04:24,500
While I was taking care
of our child,

72
00:04:24,633 --> 00:04:26,667
she was sleeping
with my husband!

73
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:28,167
Stop it, Jenny!

74
00:04:28,333 --> 00:04:29,967
Don't make a scene.
This is embarrassing!

75
00:04:31,633 --> 00:04:34,133
Please don't humiliate my child.

76
00:04:35,300 --> 00:04:38,333
You're both victims of this man.

77
00:04:38,467 --> 00:04:40,300
- My child is innocent, too!
- Mom, Mom...

78
00:04:42,367 --> 00:04:44,333
So loud! Noisy!

79
00:04:44,467 --> 00:04:46,100
I don't want this!

80
00:04:46,233 --> 00:04:48,500
- Sis!
- Let's go home!

81
00:04:48,633 --> 00:04:50,200
- We'll talk about this at home!
- No!

82
00:04:50,333 --> 00:04:52,700
I'm not done
with your mistress yet!

83
00:04:52,833 --> 00:04:57,933
You look educated, but you
went after a married man?

84
00:04:58,067 --> 00:05:00,933
You must be desperate!

85
00:05:01,100 --> 00:05:05,633
I had no idea he was married!

86
00:05:05,767 --> 00:05:08,333
If I knew, I never
would've gone near him!

87
00:05:08,467 --> 00:05:10,700
Don't wash your hands of this!

88
00:05:10,833 --> 00:05:13,267
You need to be taught a lesson!

89
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:16,300
Don't hurt her!
She didn't do anything wrong!

90
00:05:16,433 --> 00:05:17,567
Move aside, you animal!

91
00:05:17,700 --> 00:05:19,833
I'll pull all your
mistress's hair out!

92
00:05:21,600 --> 00:05:23,367
Marj!

93
00:05:24,367 --> 00:05:26,433
Let go of me, you psycho!

94
00:05:26,567 --> 00:05:30,633
This is nothing compared
to the pain you caused me!

95
00:05:30,767 --> 00:05:31,867
That's enough, Jenny!

96
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:33,233
You're so awful, girl.

97
00:05:33,367 --> 00:05:35,100
You really had to record this?

98
00:05:35,267 --> 00:05:36,633
For memories.

99
00:05:36,767 --> 00:05:39,333
Take it out on me! Not on her!
Hit me instead!

100
00:05:39,467 --> 00:05:43,133
Don't worry.
I'll deal with you later.

101
00:05:43,267 --> 00:05:46,200
But for now, I'm pulling
all your mistress's hair out!

102
00:05:46,333 --> 00:05:47,633
Move!

103
00:05:47,767 --> 00:05:51,733
So everyone can see
Marj's true colors.

104
00:05:51,867 --> 00:05:53,967
She doesn't just steal clients.

105
00:05:54,100 --> 00:05:57,033
She steals husbands, too!

106
00:05:57,167 --> 00:06:00,200
- You shameless witch!
- Let go of me!

107
00:06:02,200 --> 00:06:05,933
Wait! If you want a fight,
fight me! Not my child!

108
00:06:13,533 --> 00:06:14,600
Enough!

109
00:06:14,733 --> 00:06:16,833
Don't push me any further!

110
00:06:17,833 --> 00:06:21,267
It's too loud!

111
00:06:25,067 --> 00:06:27,967
I'm so sorry about
what happened.

112
00:06:28,100 --> 00:06:32,000
I'm really sorry. We'll just
reschedule the house tour.

113
00:06:32,133 --> 00:06:33,667
I'm sorry.

114
00:06:39,600 --> 00:06:42,033
I wasted so much time here...

115
00:06:42,200 --> 00:06:43,900
and this is what happens?

116
00:06:57,400 --> 00:06:58,633
Babe...

117
00:06:58,767 --> 00:07:00,933
Don't touch me!

118
00:07:01,067 --> 00:07:02,300
Babe.

119
00:07:02,433 --> 00:07:05,400
Don't ever call me babe again.

120
00:07:08,067 --> 00:07:10,500
I trusted you.

121
00:07:10,633 --> 00:07:12,333
I loved you.

122
00:07:13,567 --> 00:07:15,733
I thought you were the
answer to my prayers.

123
00:07:15,900 --> 00:07:20,000
And what did you do?
You lied to me, you bastard!

124
00:07:20,133 --> 00:07:21,567
No, babe.

125
00:07:21,700 --> 00:07:24,800
I admit I lied
about being single,

126
00:07:24,933 --> 00:07:29,967
but what I felt for you
was real.

127
00:07:30,100 --> 00:07:32,333
I was just scared to tell you
I had a family.

128
00:07:32,467 --> 00:07:34,167
I was afraid you'd leave me.

129
00:07:34,300 --> 00:07:40,467
You know how much pain
I've been through my whole life!

130
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:44,700
My father's mistress
destroyed our family!

131
00:07:44,833 --> 00:07:49,067
You know how much
I hate women like that!

132
00:07:49,233 --> 00:07:52,000
And without knowing it,
you turned me into one!

133
00:07:52,133 --> 00:07:54,600
You turned me into a mistress!
You lied to me!

134
00:07:54,733 --> 00:07:57,333
Everything was a lie!

135
00:07:58,433 --> 00:08:00,500
How could this happen?

136
00:08:00,633 --> 00:08:02,933
I was just the other woman!

137
00:08:05,967 --> 00:08:08,600
I thought you loved me,

138
00:08:09,967 --> 00:08:12,533
but you're just like my father.

139
00:08:18,500 --> 00:08:21,133
Don't touch me.
Don't come near me.

140
00:08:21,300 --> 00:08:22,400
Don't!

141
00:08:22,533 --> 00:08:23,933
Mister!

142
00:08:30,700 --> 00:08:33,267
Don't touch me, you animal!

143
00:09:01,833 --> 00:09:03,200
Marj.

144
00:09:04,567 --> 00:09:07,133
Don't cry over
him, sweetheart.

145
00:09:07,267 --> 00:09:09,533
You did the right thing
by leaving him.

146
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:12,500
Because...

147
00:09:12,633 --> 00:09:16,833
he lied to you.
He hurt you, Marj.

148
00:09:16,967 --> 00:09:20,333
But Mom, why didn't
I see it sooner?

149
00:09:20,467 --> 00:09:22,133
I keep replaying everything,

150
00:09:22,267 --> 00:09:23,567
trying to remember
if there were red flags.

151
00:09:23,700 --> 00:09:26,300
But I can't think of any.

152
00:09:26,433 --> 00:09:31,500
Marj, don't blame yourself
for missing the signs.

153
00:09:31,667 --> 00:09:33,867
I was the same way.

154
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:36,800
When I loved
your father that much,

155
00:09:36,933 --> 00:09:39,100
I was blind too.

156
00:09:39,233 --> 00:09:41,867
This isn't your fault.

157
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:46,767
The only one to blame
here is Randall.

158
00:09:46,900 --> 00:09:50,867
He took advantage
of your love, your trust.

159
00:09:52,267 --> 00:09:55,267
Mom, how am I supposed
to hold my head up?

160
00:09:55,400 --> 00:10:00,667
When people find out,
how am I supposed to face them?

161
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:03,000
We used to be the ones
who were wronged,

162
00:10:03,167 --> 00:10:07,200
but now I'm the one who ruined
a family.

163
00:10:07,333 --> 00:10:09,567
Mom, I'm the other woman.

164
00:10:11,067 --> 00:10:13,200
No, Marj. You're not a mistress.

165
00:10:13,333 --> 00:10:15,333
He deceived you.

166
00:10:15,467 --> 00:10:17,167
That's not the same thing.

167
00:10:17,300 --> 00:10:20,267
You didn't know
he was married.

168
00:10:42,633 --> 00:10:44,000
Sis...

169
00:10:46,667 --> 00:10:48,933
Hold Jobert.

170
00:10:49,067 --> 00:10:50,733
Hold me.

171
00:10:50,867 --> 00:10:52,233
Hold.

172
00:10:54,033 --> 00:10:56,700
When I'm sad,

173
00:10:56,833 --> 00:10:59,400
I hold Pong.

174
00:10:59,533 --> 00:11:02,133
He makes me happy.

175
00:11:07,233 --> 00:11:10,367
Don't cry, sis.

176
00:11:10,533 --> 00:11:12,767
I don't like it when you cry.

177
00:11:18,100 --> 00:11:20,233
I don't want you to cry.

178
00:11:22,567 --> 00:11:24,800
I love you, sis.

179
00:11:28,300 --> 00:11:30,500
I love you, too, Jobert.

180
00:11:36,433 --> 00:11:38,167
Stop crying now.

181
00:11:39,633 --> 00:11:42,300
I hate it when you cry.

182
00:11:57,333 --> 00:11:59,333
I won't cry anymore.

183
00:11:59,467 --> 00:12:01,500
I promise.

184
00:12:01,633 --> 00:12:03,100
Girl, tomorrow's
my last day here.

185
00:12:03,233 --> 00:12:04,200
Can we go do karaoke?

186
00:12:04,333 --> 00:12:05,700
I start working at Torrecampo
Realty next week.

187
00:12:05,833 --> 00:12:08,400
I'll be a Manila girl now.

188
00:12:11,867 --> 00:12:12,833
Girl,

189
00:12:14,767 --> 00:12:18,400
tomorrow's my last day.
Can we do karaoke?

190
00:12:18,533 --> 00:12:22,000
I start at Torrecampo
Realty next week.

191
00:12:25,933 --> 00:12:27,467
Hey, what's wrong with you?

192
00:12:27,600 --> 00:12:28,967
You've been spaced out all day.

193
00:12:29,100 --> 00:12:31,200
You look so down.
Is something bothering you?

194
00:12:35,633 --> 00:12:37,433
Excuse me, Hannah.

195
00:12:40,433 --> 00:12:41,400
Marj,

196
00:12:43,033 --> 00:12:44,733
can we talk?

197
00:12:47,433 --> 00:12:51,167
Girl, let's just continue
our chat later, okay?

198
00:12:56,800 --> 00:12:59,833
There's nothing left
for us to talk about, Randall.

199
00:13:02,533 --> 00:13:04,533
You should just return my share

200
00:13:04,667 --> 00:13:05,767
of the down payment
on the house.

201
00:13:05,900 --> 00:13:08,100
I don't plan
on living there anymore.

202
00:13:09,667 --> 00:13:11,067
Marj...

203
00:13:13,967 --> 00:13:16,100
I don't want us
to end like this.

204
00:13:17,467 --> 00:13:19,933
Just give me a chance.

205
00:13:20,067 --> 00:13:21,700
Let's talk. Let's fix this.

206
00:13:21,867 --> 00:13:23,467
Randall,
do you even hear yourself?

207
00:13:23,600 --> 00:13:26,600
What is there left to fix?

208
00:13:26,733 --> 00:13:30,000
You lied to me for two years!

209
00:13:30,133 --> 00:13:31,100
What do you want me to do?

210
00:13:31,233 --> 00:13:32,767
Stay and be your mistress?

211
00:13:34,233 --> 00:13:37,000
Sorry, but I'm not
that desperate.

212
00:13:37,133 --> 00:13:40,600
And more than anything,
I respect myself.

213
00:13:41,733 --> 00:13:43,167
Marj, Randall.

214
00:13:43,300 --> 00:13:46,400
Boss James is calling you both
to his office.

215
00:14:03,967 --> 00:14:05,700
<i> I'll make your mistress bald!</i>

216
00:14:05,833 --> 00:14:07,533
<i> Ouch!</i>

217
00:14:07,667 --> 00:14:09,033
<i>- It hurts!
- Jenny!</i>

218
00:14:09,167 --> 00:14:10,233
<i> Marj!</i>

219
00:14:10,367 --> 00:14:14,033
<i>That is nothing compared to the
pain of your betrayal!</i>

220
00:14:14,167 --> 00:14:18,733
<i>- Get off of me! It hurts!
- Jenny, stop it! Stop!</i>

221
00:14:21,333 --> 00:14:22,500
<i> Hurt me, not her!</i>

222
00:14:27,900 --> 00:14:29,600
Why do you have a copy of it?

223
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:33,000
Who sent you the video?

224
00:14:33,133 --> 00:14:36,800
Who sent it, isn't important.

225
00:14:36,933 --> 00:14:38,100
The issue here

226
00:14:38,233 --> 00:14:41,633
is that the two of you were
involved in an illicit affair.

227
00:14:41,767 --> 00:14:45,300
Sir, this is a personal matter.

228
00:14:45,433 --> 00:14:47,167
It has nothing to do with work.

229
00:14:48,533 --> 00:14:54,167
Clients could lose trust
in you if this gets out.

230
00:14:54,300 --> 00:14:57,600
If that happens,
our sales will drop.

231
00:14:57,733 --> 00:15:02,467
Aside from that, the company's
image will be damaged.

232
00:15:02,633 --> 00:15:05,600
And I can't let that happen.

233
00:15:05,733 --> 00:15:08,200
Why not just be straight
with us?

234
00:15:08,333 --> 00:15:11,200
Are we being suspended?

235
00:15:11,333 --> 00:15:12,667
I'm sorry.

236
00:15:12,800 --> 00:15:15,367
But I can't tolerate
what you did.

237
00:15:15,500 --> 00:15:18,833
I have to set an example
so this doesn't happen again.

238
00:15:18,967 --> 00:15:22,733
That's why I've decided
to let you both go.

239
00:15:22,867 --> 00:15:24,533
Wait, Sir.

240
00:15:24,667 --> 00:15:26,733
Marj didn't do
anything wrong.

241
00:15:26,867 --> 00:15:27,733
She didn't know I was married.

242
00:15:27,867 --> 00:15:28,433
Please don't involve her.

243
00:15:28,567 --> 00:15:30,933
Punish me instead.

244
00:15:31,067 --> 00:15:32,733
I'm really sorry.

245
00:15:32,867 --> 00:15:37,500
I'm just following what's
written in the company handbook.

246
00:15:37,667 --> 00:15:39,400
There's nothing I can do.

247
00:15:46,533 --> 00:15:48,233
Thank you!

248
00:15:48,367 --> 00:15:52,300
Don't worry, I'll treat you all
tonight now that

249
00:15:57,733 --> 00:15:59,000
Oh, friend.

250
00:15:59,133 --> 00:16:01,667
Have you heard the rumor?

251
00:16:01,800 --> 00:16:06,067
Those OFW clients
canceled buying property.

252
00:16:06,200 --> 00:16:10,100
The agent they were
talking to turned them off.

253
00:16:10,267 --> 00:16:14,100
Apparently, she was messing
around with a married man.

254
00:16:14,233 --> 00:16:15,367
Exactly.

255
00:16:15,500 --> 00:16:18,000
That's why it was good
we showed the video to them

256
00:16:18,133 --> 00:16:20,733
and to our boss...

257
00:16:20,867 --> 00:16:22,033
Be quiet!

258
00:16:22,167 --> 00:16:23,533
That was your video?

259
00:16:25,233 --> 00:16:26,867
Why did you do that?

260
00:16:27,900 --> 00:16:30,400
Why did you spread it?

261
00:16:33,900 --> 00:16:35,500
Marj,

262
00:16:35,633 --> 00:16:37,867
I didn't want to do it.

263
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:41,333
But I was worried
about the company's image.

264
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:43,267
A lot more people
could've been affected.

265
00:16:43,400 --> 00:16:44,700
<i> Remember this, Marj.</i>

266
00:16:44,833 --> 00:16:46,267
<i> You started this. Not me.</i>

267
00:16:46,400 --> 00:16:48,533
<i>Now you're seeing
the real Thea.</i>

268
00:16:48,667 --> 00:16:50,833
<i> You'll regret crossing me.</i>

269
00:16:53,367 --> 00:16:55,200
Don't lie to me, Thea!

270
00:16:55,333 --> 00:16:56,567
Just admit it.

271
00:16:56,700 --> 00:16:58,800
You did it to ruin me!

272
00:16:58,933 --> 00:17:02,000
So you could take back
the clients you lost!

273
00:17:02,133 --> 00:17:03,933
Why did you do this to me?

274
00:17:04,067 --> 00:17:06,700
Let go of me!
You're hurting me!

275
00:17:06,833 --> 00:17:09,067
You know what?
I didn't just lose my job!

276
00:17:09,200 --> 00:17:12,467
Did you even think about
how this would affect my family?

277
00:17:12,600 --> 00:17:14,733
It's not just me
who lost a career.

278
00:17:14,900 --> 00:17:17,100
Even the people
who depend on me!

279
00:17:17,233 --> 00:17:18,900
And why are you blaming me?

280
00:17:19,033 --> 00:17:21,100
Aren't you the one
who did something wrong?

281
00:17:21,233 --> 00:17:22,133
If you didn't want
to get fired,

282
00:17:22,267 --> 00:17:24,367
you shouldn't have done
something immoral!

283
00:17:24,500 --> 00:17:27,100
So that's how you see me, huh?

284
00:17:27,233 --> 00:17:29,367
Don't interfere!
I'll slap you!

285
00:17:30,967 --> 00:17:33,733
This is exactly where trash
like you belongs!

286
00:17:33,867 --> 00:17:35,033
No! Don't!

287
00:17:38,633 --> 00:17:40,233
Face me!

288
00:17:40,367 --> 00:17:42,967
Be thankful I'm not as cruel
as you are.

289
00:17:43,100 --> 00:17:47,100
But this is the last time
I'm letting it slide.

290
00:17:47,233 --> 00:17:50,267
Next time you mess with me,

291
00:17:50,433 --> 00:17:53,100
I'll do something
much worse to you.

292
00:18:00,900 --> 00:18:02,300
Are you okay?

293
00:18:27,433 --> 00:18:28,600
<i> I can't take this anymore!</i>

294
00:18:28,733 --> 00:18:29,433
<i> You're all a bunch of pests!</i>

295
00:18:29,567 --> 00:18:30,767
<i> Nothing but trouble!</i>

296
00:18:33,033 --> 00:18:35,567
Why did you let that kid
out of the room?

297
00:18:35,700 --> 00:18:37,800
If you'd watched
your child properly,

298
00:18:37,933 --> 00:18:40,067
he wouldn't have broken the
decoration in the living room!

299
00:18:40,200 --> 00:18:41,867
Wait, Hilda.

300
00:18:42,000 --> 00:18:44,200
Please don't raise
your voice at Mom.

301
00:18:44,333 --> 00:18:46,400
You could talk to her calmly.

302
00:18:46,533 --> 00:18:47,867
It's their fault!

303
00:18:49,367 --> 00:18:50,233
What even happened here?

304
00:18:50,367 --> 00:18:54,267
Your brother's pet turtle
got out.

305
00:18:54,400 --> 00:18:55,600
He went looking for it,

306
00:18:55,767 --> 00:18:57,967
and that's how he broke
the vase.

307
00:18:58,100 --> 00:19:00,633
I didn't mean to.

308
00:19:00,767 --> 00:19:01,967
I was just chasing Pong.

309
00:19:02,100 --> 00:19:03,467
I didn't mean to.

310
00:19:03,600 --> 00:19:05,567
Hey! Have some shame!

311
00:19:05,700 --> 00:19:07,167
I already let you stay here,

312
00:19:07,300 --> 00:19:09,433
and now you're breaking our
things?

313
00:19:12,600 --> 00:19:16,433
If I'd known your brother
would be this much trouble,

314
00:19:17,767 --> 00:19:20,767
I would've thought twice
about letting you stay here!

315
00:19:21,933 --> 00:19:24,033
What's happening?

316
00:19:27,633 --> 00:19:28,833
Hey, what's going on with him?

317
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:30,367
He has epilepsy, Hilda.

318
00:19:30,500 --> 00:19:32,167
Stress triggers his seizures.

319
00:19:32,300 --> 00:19:35,433
So please,
if Jobert makes a mistake,

320
00:19:35,567 --> 00:19:38,067
talk to my mom or me instead.

321
00:19:38,200 --> 00:19:42,133
Hold him tightly before
he breaks more of our stuff!

322
00:19:42,267 --> 00:19:44,767
My God, all you do is bring
problems into this house!

323
00:19:44,900 --> 00:19:46,667
I'm out of here!

324
00:19:57,600 --> 00:20:01,900
Marj, maybe we should start
looking for another place.

325
00:20:02,067 --> 00:20:03,467
Jobert can't stay
here anymore.

326
00:20:03,600 --> 00:20:07,100
He's always stressed because
of Hilda's constant yelling.

327
00:20:10,800 --> 00:20:12,133
Why, Marj?

328
00:20:19,067 --> 00:20:20,800
I'm sorry, Mom.

329
00:20:23,667 --> 00:20:25,767
I lost my job.

330
00:20:28,333 --> 00:20:30,167
This is my fault.

331
00:20:30,300 --> 00:20:33,300
If I hadn't let Randall fool me,

332
00:20:33,433 --> 00:20:35,900
we wouldn't be
in this situation.

333
00:20:38,467 --> 00:20:39,733
But don't worry, Mom.

334
00:20:39,867 --> 00:20:41,733
I'll figure something out.

335
00:20:41,867 --> 00:20:43,533
I can handle this.

336
00:20:43,667 --> 00:20:46,167
I'll find us a new place.

337
00:20:49,900 --> 00:20:51,533
Unbelievable.

338
00:20:51,667 --> 00:20:54,033
It's like misfortune
keeps hitting you nonstop, girl.

339
00:20:54,167 --> 00:20:55,467
Can you still breathe?

340
00:20:57,167 --> 00:20:58,667
It's okay.

341
00:20:58,800 --> 00:21:01,100
It's okay if I struggle
and get tired.

342
00:21:01,233 --> 00:21:03,967
But I can't give up.

343
00:21:04,100 --> 00:21:07,400
I have to keep my promise
to Mom and Jobert.

344
00:21:07,533 --> 00:21:09,967
A better life,

345
00:21:10,133 --> 00:21:11,833
our dream home.

346
00:21:13,933 --> 00:21:17,267
And I'll do whatever it takes
to make that happen.

347
00:21:17,400 --> 00:21:18,967
That's right, girl.

348
00:21:19,100 --> 00:21:20,667
Just keep going.

349
00:21:20,800 --> 00:21:21,900
I just hope

350
00:21:22,033 --> 00:21:24,667
your loud-mouthed cousin
doesn't add to your problems.

351
00:21:26,367 --> 00:21:29,700
It's no longer safe
for Jobert to stay there.

352
00:21:29,833 --> 00:21:32,800
I need to find us a new place.

353
00:21:34,767 --> 00:21:37,500
But I can't do that
until I get a new job.

354
00:21:39,033 --> 00:21:40,367
Why don't you apply

355
00:21:40,500 --> 00:21:42,200
to the company
I'm transferring to?

356
00:21:42,367 --> 00:21:43,533
The Torrecampo Realty.

357
00:21:43,667 --> 00:21:45,267
The pay is better.

358
00:21:45,400 --> 00:21:47,800
And if you move to Manila,

359
00:21:47,933 --> 00:21:50,400
there are more schools there
for special-needs kids.

360
00:21:50,533 --> 00:21:51,833
Jobert could go there.

361
00:22:11,067 --> 00:22:12,800
Hello, good afternoon.

362
00:22:12,933 --> 00:22:14,500
Good afternoon, Miss Castillo.

363
00:22:14,633 --> 00:22:16,167
We're calling about the job
application you emailed.

364
00:22:16,333 --> 00:22:17,767
We received it.

365
00:22:17,900 --> 00:22:19,500
And we're impressed
with your résumé.

366
00:22:19,633 --> 00:22:23,167
We'd like to invite you
for an interview.

367
00:22:23,300 --> 00:22:25,233
When would the interview be?

368
00:22:25,367 --> 00:22:28,800
Next week. But you'll need
to be here in person.

369
00:22:28,933 --> 00:22:31,133
It's a face-to-face interview.

370
00:22:31,267 --> 00:22:32,467
That won't be a problem.

371
00:22:32,600 --> 00:22:33,733
I'll come to Manila.

372
00:22:33,867 --> 00:22:35,200
All right. See you then.

373
00:22:35,333 --> 00:22:37,333
Thank you so much.

374
00:23:02,067 --> 00:23:04,567
You said you had something
important to tell me.

375
00:23:05,200 --> 00:23:06,000
Just say it straight.

376
00:23:06,133 --> 00:23:07,233
I don't have time.

377
00:23:07,367 --> 00:23:08,333
I want to go home.

378
00:23:16,900 --> 00:23:17,767
I'm sorry.

379
00:23:19,300 --> 00:23:21,067
This is all the cash
I can give you for now.

380
00:23:22,933 --> 00:23:23,633
But...

381
00:23:24,300 --> 00:23:28,000
once I find a buyer to take over
the house we were paying for,

382
00:23:29,900 --> 00:23:31,400
I'll return the rest.

383
00:23:38,433 --> 00:23:42,000
Marj, I understand if you never
want to see me again.

384
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:46,333
But before I go...

385
00:23:48,300 --> 00:23:49,600
I just want you to know...

386
00:23:52,367 --> 00:23:53,333
I'm truly sorry.

387
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:57,467
I'll regret hurting you
for the rest of my life.

388
00:24:02,133 --> 00:24:03,933
I wish I had met you sooner.

389
00:24:05,867 --> 00:24:07,567
I wish we'd met
when I was still free.

390
00:24:12,967 --> 00:24:14,367
I love you so much, Marj.

391
00:24:18,967 --> 00:24:21,100
I know loving you was wrong...

392
00:24:23,467 --> 00:24:26,067
but the time we spent together

393
00:24:26,200 --> 00:24:29,533
was the happiest time
of my life.

394
00:24:39,567 --> 00:24:40,600
Goodbye, Marj.

395
00:24:45,800 --> 00:24:47,433
I'll never forget you.

396
00:25:57,100 --> 00:25:58,000
Mom.

397
00:25:59,300 --> 00:26:00,067
It's really late.

398
00:26:01,100 --> 00:26:02,567
You still haven't rested.

399
00:26:02,700 --> 00:26:05,833
I'm just checking the
travel schedule to Manila.

400
00:26:07,600 --> 00:26:09,733
Marj, are you sure about this?

401
00:26:09,900 --> 00:26:10,900
Yes, Mom.

402
00:26:11,033 --> 00:26:15,267
Once I get this job,
I'll find us a place right away

403
00:26:15,400 --> 00:26:16,867
and bring you
and Jobert there.

404
00:26:17,733 --> 00:26:19,800
I promise, you won't have
to endure staying here anymore.

405
00:26:22,233 --> 00:26:27,433
But there's another reason
I really want to do this.

406
00:26:29,333 --> 00:26:34,733
It's the only way I know
how to leave everything behind.

407
00:26:36,267 --> 00:26:37,300
The demolition.

408
00:26:38,567 --> 00:26:40,100
Losing my job.

409
00:26:40,233 --> 00:26:42,467
And Randall.

410
00:26:45,533 --> 00:26:48,133
Please forgive me.

411
00:26:49,400 --> 00:26:52,767
I know you're carrying
all of this on your shoulders.

412
00:26:54,400 --> 00:26:55,000
I'm the mother.

413
00:26:55,133 --> 00:26:57,067
I should be the one responsible.

414
00:26:58,500 --> 00:27:00,733
But ever since your father
and I separated,

415
00:27:02,500 --> 00:27:03,867
I have become weak.

416
00:27:05,933 --> 00:27:10,433
Mom, what happened with Randall
broke me, too.

417
00:27:12,133 --> 00:27:14,033
But I chose to be strong.

418
00:27:15,100 --> 00:27:17,900
Because I know people
are depending on me.

419
00:27:19,600 --> 00:27:22,533
So please, Mom,
choose to be strong, too.

420
00:27:23,733 --> 00:27:25,433
Because I can't do this alone.

421
00:27:27,633 --> 00:27:29,033
I still need my mom.

422
00:27:48,700 --> 00:27:50,233
For Mom and Jobert.

423
00:27:51,500 --> 00:27:52,433
I can do this.

424
00:27:55,333 --> 00:27:57,767
Friend, I'm only asking
for one favor.

425
00:27:58,667 --> 00:27:59,733
Just this once.

426
00:28:00,800 --> 00:28:02,367
You received the video, right?

427
00:28:03,067 --> 00:28:05,900
<i>Isn't that enough reason
to turn down Marj's application?</i>

428
00:28:06,467 --> 00:28:10,500
Thea, I can't reject
Miss Castillo's application.

429
00:28:12,467 --> 00:28:14,400
That's why we conduct
interviews,

430
00:28:14,533 --> 00:28:16,633
to hear their side.

431
00:28:16,767 --> 00:28:18,633
What else do you want to know?

432
00:28:18,767 --> 00:28:20,800
It's all there in the video.

433
00:28:20,933 --> 00:28:23,233
She's a mistress,
and she's violent.

434
00:28:23,400 --> 00:28:24,700
Is that really the kind
of employee

435
00:28:24,833 --> 00:28:26,300
Torrecampo Realty wants?

436
00:28:46,333 --> 00:28:51,300
We'll contact all her references
to assess her properly, okay?

437
00:28:52,067 --> 00:28:53,000
But I'm sorry, Thea.

438
00:28:53,133 --> 00:28:54,833
I can't grant your request
right now.

439
00:29:04,467 --> 00:29:08,367
She needs to close this sale,
or it's goodbye.

440
00:29:08,500 --> 00:29:09,767
Sir, do you need something?

441
00:29:09,900 --> 00:29:12,733
I'm hoping to ask you out.

442
00:29:12,867 --> 00:29:13,700
You're not allowed to say no.

443
00:29:13,833 --> 00:29:16,100
We can talk
about the properties later.

444
00:29:16,233 --> 00:29:17,700
There's something else I want.

445
00:29:17,833 --> 00:29:18,700
Excuse me.

446
00:29:18,833 --> 00:29:19,933
I just need to grab
something upstairs.

447
00:29:21,267 --> 00:29:22,067
Pervert!

448
00:29:23,267 --> 00:29:24,033
What is this?

449
00:29:24,167 --> 00:29:27,000
In our business,
the client is king.

450
00:29:27,133 --> 00:29:30,000
She had no right to disrespect
and assault Mr. Balderamas.

451
00:29:30,167 --> 00:29:31,800
Sir, I'm the victim here.

452
00:29:31,933 --> 00:29:33,400
Gather your things.

453
00:29:33,533 --> 00:29:35,433
Get out of here
because you're fired!
